  "output": "Good picture now. No frontend yet (no `.svelte`/`.ts` files) — Sprint 1 is pure Python core. No N+1 DB queries exist (no DB layer yet). Analysis focuses on actual Python hot paths.\n\n---\n\n## Performance Analysis\n\n### 1. Double iteration in `advance_shipments` — `order_processor.py:7-13`\n\nTwo passes over `incoming_shipments` per player per round:\n\n```python\n# Current — two passes\narrived = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1)\nps.incoming_shipments = [\n    IncomingShipment(quantity=s.quantity, arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1)\n    for s in ps.incoming_shipments\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds > 1\n]\n```\n\nFix — single pass:\n\n```python\narrived = 0\nkept = []\nfor s in ps.incoming_shipments:\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1:\n        arrived += s.quantity\n    else:\n        s.arrives_in_rounds -= 1  # mutate in-place (Pydantic v2 allows it)\n        kept.append(s)\nps.inventory += arrived\nps.incoming_shipments = kept\n```\n\nEliminates N new `IncomingShipment` Pydantic model instantiations (validation overhead) per round per player.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `is_round_complete()` rebuilds active-roles set on every call — `game.py:56-57`\n\n```python\ndef is_round_complete(self) -> bool:\n    active_roles = {role for role, ps in self.players.items() if not ps.is_ai}\n    return active_roles.issubset(self.orders_this_round.keys())\n```\n\nCalled on every WebSocket message. Active roles never change mid-game. Cache it:\n\n```python\nclass GameState(BaseModel):\n    ...\n    _active_roles: set[PlayerRole] | None = None  # private, not serialized\n\n    def active_human_roles(self) -> set[PlayerRole]:\n        if self._active_roles is None:\n            self._active_roles = {r for r, ps in self.players.items() if not ps.is_ai}\n        return self._active_roles\n\n    def is_round_complete(self) -> bool:\n        return self.active_human_roles().issubset(self.orders_this_round.keys())\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `incoming_orders` list grows unbounded — `order_processor.py:72`\n\n```python\nupstream_ps.incoming_orders.append(order_qty)\n```\n\nAfter 26 rounds factory has 25 entries, never consumed. Only `last_order` is ever read. Either clear it after each round or drop the list entirely — nothing reads `incoming_orders` in the current codebase.\n\nFix in `place_orders`:\n\n```python\n# Replace append with direct assignment; drop incoming_orders list\nupstream_ps.last_order = order_qty  # or keep separate received_order field\n```\n\nOr clear at end of `process_round`:\n\n```python\nfor ps in state.players.values():\n    ps.incoming_orders.clear()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Correctness bug with perf impact — `game.py:41-42` vs `order_processor.py:87-90`\n\n`PlayerState.round_cost()` uses module-level constants:\n\n```python\ndef round_cost(self) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT + self.backlog * BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT\n```\n\n`accrue_costs` uses `state.config.holding_cost`. With non-default `GameConfig`, these diverge — `round_cost()` returns wrong values. Fix requires passing config or removing `round_cost()` and calling `accrue_costs` exclusively.\n\n---\n\n### 5. No N+1, no React re-renders, no memory leaks (yet)\n\n- No DB layer exists — N+1 patterns irrelevant until FastAPI + PostgreSQL land\n- No frontend — no React/Svelte re-render issues\n- No memory leaks — `GameState` is value-typed, no global mutable caches, no circular refs\n\n---\n\n**Priority order:** Issue 3 (unbounded list) is the only one that compounds over time. Issue 1 reduces GC pressure. Issues 2 and 4 are correctness fixes that happen to be cheaper.\n",
